MobileCause Inc. Key Developments

MobileCause Appoints Alan Park as Senior Vice President of Enterprise Sales
Jun 8 17
MobileCause has hired Alan Park to lead the company’s enterprise sales team as Senior Vice President. This key hire comes at a pivotal time in the company’s growth where it has recently received Series B Funding to invest in growth initiatives including product development, customer support and digital marketing services that will help nonprofit organizations enhance their fundraising efforts. Park is a seasoned sales executive coming to MobileCause with a wealth of experience having spent more than 30 years in the software industry and most recently was the Chief Revenue Officer for Affectiva. While at Affectiva, he closed strategic global accounts in new verticals and established global distribution partnerships to accelerate growth. As a highly accomplished sales executive, Alan brings decades of experience identifying industry dynamics and rapidly adapting sales organizations to address unmet needs.


MobileCause Appoints Kristal Bogle as the New Chief Marketing Officer
Mar 30 17
MobileCause announced Kristal Bogle as the company's new Chief Marketing Officer. Kristal will spearhead all aspects of marketing, including branding, product marketing, digital and inbound marketing, events, public relations and communications. She is a respected marketer and thought leader in data-driven marketing, with nearly 20 years of experience.


MobileCause Appoints Tim Kane as Member of Executive Team
Mar 30 17
MobileCause announced that with Tim Kane's leadership as a member of the MobileCause executive team and in his role of Senior Vice President of SMB Sales, he has led exponential growth of the SMB sales team over the first quarter of 2017. A highly accomplished sales professional, Tim brings more than twenty years of industry experience driving new business development and revenue growth.


