 MobileCause Announces Q2 2017 Product Release to Advance Hub for Nonprofit Fundraising and Donor Engagement




                    Wednesday, July 19, 2017 4:27 PM  UTC                                            
0 comments                        



Los Angeles, CA, July  19, 2017   -- LOS ANGELES, CA – July 19, 2017 – MobileCause, a leading provider of fundraising and donor engagement software for nonprofit organizations, today announced enhancements and features launched with its Q2 2017 product release, designed to help nonprofits easily use technology for all their fundraising needs. The release enables customers to access fundraising, events, communication and marketing solutions, as well as reporting tools, all in one single hub.


















 In recent industry surveys, nonprofit organizations voice that they are continually seeking ways to consolidate their many technology solutions to more efficiently support their day-to-day needs. Because of this, MobileCause consolidates more than twenty-five fundraising, donor communication, event support and payment processing point solutions into a single platform, making it more time and cost-efficient to raise money as well as provide a consistent donor experience. “Gone are the days of multiple logins, inconsistent donor records and file sharing between countless nonprofit fundraising tools,” said Sean MacNeill, MobileCause CEO. “Through our engagement platform, we have helped thousands of nonprofit organizations communicate effectively with current donors, acquire new donors and inspire more recurring donations.” Additionally, MobileCause offers a simple way for fundraisers to set up and promote their own crowdfunding campaign. The company recognized the growing interest in crowdfunding and the ability for nonprofits to inspire donors to do more than just give by also encouraging friends, family and others to support their cause. More and more customers have adopted the crowdfunding feature because it’s flexible enough to maintain a nonprofit’s brand consistency while allowing the individual fundraiser to easily encourage others to donate or participate. The platform’s navigation has been restructured to reflect the tasks that are most common for nonprofits when setting up fundraising events and campaigns. The user experience now quickly leads them through the platform to more easily accomplish campaign setup, execution and follow-up. This user-centric approach is the first step in a line of planned enhancements to better support the urgency in fundraising for nonprofit organizations. These product announcements come at a time of increasing acceleration for MobileCause, which received a $15 million investment from Level Equity earlier this year. To learn more, visit mobilecause.com.   About MobileCause, Inc. MobileCause provides an innovative suite of digital fundraising and donor engagement solutions that help nonprofits do more good with a full suite of customizable, mobile-friendly solutions including online forms, fundraising events, crowdfunding, campaign promotion, data management, and credit card processing with zero transaction fees. MobileCause is trusted by thousands of nonprofit organizations including United Way, The Salvation Army, American Heart Association, University of Southern California, Habitat for Humanity and many more. Attachments:    A photo accompanying this announcement is available at http://www.globenewswire.com/NewsRoom/AttachmentNg/7c816c7c-4e41-41d6-8099-d21d3e39e825 
Kristal Bogle
MobileCause
4243135630
kristal@mobilecause.com












